                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="439576" author="pjones" created="Mon, 23 Dec 2024 14:22:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.15.6 GA including the fix in question&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="435672" author="pjones" created="Tue, 19 Nov 2024 00:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix merged for 2.15.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430467" author="adilger" created="Tue, 8 Oct 2024 00:52:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ofaaland&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ofaaland&quot;&gt;ofaaland&lt;/a&gt;, yes, this patch increases the mjnimum per-object limit from 2TiB to 16TiB for objects that are not initialized. For ZFS this limit would not apply, but the client doesn&apos;t know the objects are on ZFS until after they are allocated. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430450" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2024 22:56:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please confirm this patch is the correct fix.&#160; It appears to work in our testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430449" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2024 22:55:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Eric Carbonneau pushed a backport for b2_15:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56100&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56100&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430448" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2024 22:54:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We believe this to be the same as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17573&quot; title=&quot;lets use ext4 limit for uninitiated object.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17573&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17573&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
